.TH "vmap_pfn" 9 "vmap_pfn" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmap_pfn \- map an array of PFNs into virtually contiguous space
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" vmap_pfn
.BI "(unsigned long *pfns "  ","
.BI "unsigned int count "  ","
.BI "pgprot_t prot "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pfns" 12
array of PFNs
.IP "count" 12
number of pages to map
.IP "prot" 12
page protection for the mapping
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Maps \fIcount\fP PFNs from \fIpfns\fP into contiguous kernel virtual space and returns
the start address of the mapping.
